TRANSLATION :
<br />Chief of the Defence Intelligence of Ukraine Major General Kyrylo Budanov: Russians have enough missile stocks for two or three more massive attacks on Ukraine
<br />
<br />- Under very favorable conditions, Russians can produce up to 50 X-101 and Kalibr missiles per month. That is, for one missile attack on Ukraine, Russians need to work for one and a half to two months, - Kyrylo Budanov said.
<br />
<br />Also, the engine resource of Russian aircrafts is being exhausted.
<br />
<br />- Strategic bombers-missile carriers have to cover quite a long distance to launch missiles. Now Russian bombers do not approach the usual areas of attack: they take off, make a circle or two in the sky and launch missiles practically over the airfield to reduce the aircraft&#39;s engine life.
<br />
<br />According to him, Russia currently has about 70 bombers: Tu-160 and Tu-95. They have about 70-80 units of Tu-22M. About 40% of them are faulty.
<br />

<br />Within half an hour, the police found a man who was launching fireworks on New Year&#39;s Eve
<br />
<br />On January 1, the police of Vinnytsia region identified and delivered to the police unit a resident of Vinnytsia, who was launching pyrotechnics around 00.30. The investigation is underway.
<br />
<br />On January 1, around 00.30, the police received a report of violation of the ban on the use of fireworks. According to the head of the Police Department No. 1 of the Vinnytsia District Police Department Yuriy Holub, the person involved in the offense was identified by the police with the help of witnesses. It was a 45-year-old resident of Vinnytsia.

<br />
<br />Ukraine Now journalist talked to one of the most famous defenders of Bakhmut. According to &#34;Kyianyn&#34;, earlier Russians attacked with large units and armored vehicles, but closer to winter they began to attack with smaller assault groups. There were 30-40, and now there are 7-10 people. They are trying to get under the cover of mortars and artillery, to push the positions, but the Ukrainian Armed Forces are always ready for this.
<br />
<br />&#34;Kyianyn&#34; says that enemy subversive reconnaissance groups that manage to get into Bakhmut are immediately eliminated by our &#34;flying groups&#34;. This situation is predictable for Ukrainian soldiers, because there is no continuous front line of 200 km of trenches and therefore &#34;it is a normal working situation&#34;. The &#34;Kyivan&#34; also told what he thinks about the &#34;Wagnerites&#34; and their leader Prigozhin.
<br />
<br />&#34;We had captured &#34;Wagnerites&#34;. To say that they are some kind of superhumans - there is absolutely no such thing. PMCs are fighting only for money. <br />RCH 155 is a 155 mm self-propelled artillery system with remote control, developed by the German company Krauss-Maffei Wegmann in 2014. <br />‚ûû Install the recommended application (available on iOS and Android);

<br />
<br />The requirements for retirement at age 60 will grow in Ukraine for another five years.
<br />
<br />As a result, already in 2028 only those Ukrainians who have at least 35 years of experience will be able to receive a payment in time.

<br />‚ùóÔ∏èEvery working person can calculate his or her retirement age now:

<br />

TRANSLATION :
<br />Vitali Klitschko:
<br />
<br />Briefly about the life of the capital over the past day.
<br />
<br />New Year&#39;s Eve was restless. After the daytime shelling, the Russians struck at the capital at night.
<br />
<br />Thus, on the night of January 1, 2023, two cases of rocket debris falling were recorded. In Shevchenkivskyi district, a car was damaged, in Dniprovskyi district, the fall of debris did not cause any damage. In both cases, fortunately, there were no casualties.
<br />
<br />In Podilskyi district of the city, despite repeated warnings from law enforcement agencies, there were people who wanted to shoot fireworks. According to the police, a local resident ignored the ban on the use of pyrotechnic products during martial law. The man, who was launching fireworks, was detained. Now he faces up to five years in prison.
<br />
<br />At night, the city, in addition to the police, was patrolled by the &#34;Municipal Guard&#34; of the capital. Its 149 employees were on daily duty. 17 mobile rapid response teams were patrolling the city, including 15 crews on New Year&#39;s Eve.
<br />
<br />At night, the &#34;Municipal Guard&#34; of Kyiv detected 116 curfew violators. Their documents were checked, one of the violators was handed over to the National Police.
<br />
<br />Also, 12 rescuers of the Kyiv Rescue Service participated in the elimination of the consequences of the shelling of the capital. In total, the rescuers made 8 calls per day.

<br />New Year&#39;s Eve in the capital: Falling rocket fragments, fireworks and curfew violators
<br />
<br />&#34;New Year&#39;s Eve was restless. After the shelling during the day, the Russians struck at the capital at night,&#34; Kyiv Mayor Vitali Klitschko said in Telegram.
<br />
<br />üöÄ Thus, on the night of January 1, two cases of rocket debris falling were recorded. In the Shevchenkivskyi district, a car was damaged, in the Dnipro district, the fall of debris did not cause damage. In both cases, there were no casualties. 12 rescuers of the municipal emergency rescue service &#34;Kyiv Rescue Service&#34; participated in the elimination of the consequences of the shelling of the capital. In total, the rescuers made 8 visits per day.
<br />
<br />üí• In Podilskyi district of the city, despite repeated warnings from law enforcement agencies, there were people who wanted to shoot fireworks. According to the police, a local resident ignored the ban on the use of pyrotechnic products during martial law. The man, who was launching fireworks, was detained. Now he faces up to five years in prison.
<br />
<br />üïê At night, the &#34;Municipal Guard&#34; of Kyiv detected 116 curfew violators. Their documents were checked, one of them was handed over to the National Police.

TRANSLATION :
<br />Consequences of night shelling of the only hospital in Kherson providing round-the-clock medical aid to children
<br />
<br />In the first minutes of the New Year, Russia struck another terrorist attack - the enemy fired about 7 shells at the Kherson Regional Children&#39;s Clinical Hospital, said the head of the Kherson Regional Military Administration Yanushevych. The thoracic department of the neonatal building was heavily damaged, two intensive care wards were destroyed and other medical rooms of the main building were damaged. In total, more than 700 windows were broken in the hospital.
<br />
<br />Because of the racist attack, a fire broke out - a nurse&#39;s office and a ward for patients were burning.
<br />
<br />The hospital staff evacuated 17 children, 4 parents and 38 hospital employees to the shelter. This allowed to avoid casualties among civilians.

<br />

<br />üìçFrom January 1, the pension fund will start, accrue and pay subsidies and benefits, sick pay;

<br />üìç Due to the full-scale war in Ukraine, the state budget for 2023 does not provide for an increase in the minimum wage and the cost of living;

<br />
<br />Around midnight, the capital&#39;s police received several reports from citizens that unknown persons were launching fireworks in the Podil district. The corresponding video with fireworks was also spread in many telegram channels.

<br />In the evening of December 31, in the village of Buzke, a woman went into labor. An ambulance was sent, but it got stuck in the mud, and the State Emergency Service was sent to help. They connected a midwife from Nova Odesa and gave birth via Skype.

TRANSLATION :
<br />The 114th anniversary of Stepan Bandera was celebrated in Lviv
<br />
<br />Hundreds of Lviv residents gathered on January 1 at the monument to Stepan Bandera to commemorate the 114th anniversary of the birth of the leader of the Organization of Ukrainian Nationalists, Radio Liberty reports. This year, due to security measures, the traditional assembly and marches were not held. Also, the organizers of the marches in Lviv are now defending Ukraine.
<br />
<br />&#34;Now, in the active phase of the Russian-Ukrainian war, Russia is creating another myth about Bandera, the enemy reduces everything to the fact that every Ukrainian is a Bandera supporter. Unfortunately, many people in Ukraine do not know about Bandera, it all comes down to the song &#34;Our Father Bandera&#34;. The association of Bandera and the war is activated at such a moment and Bandera is a symbol of the liberation struggle, regardless of whether a citizen is for or against Bandera,&#34; - historian, researcher of the history of the OUN and UPA Mykola Posivnych said.

TRANSLATION :
<br />‚ùóÔ∏è The Social Insurance Fund in Ukraine ceased operations
<br />
<br />üìåThe Cabinet of Ministers has decided to terminate the activity of the Social Insurance Fund in Ukraine, Prime Minister Denis Shmigal said.
<br />
<br />üó£&#34;We continue social reform. Today by a governmental decision in compliance with the law we are terminating the activity of the Social Insurance Fund and joining it to the Pension Fund of Ukraine,&#34; - said the head of the government.

TRANSLATION :
<br />Payments for IDPs will be automatically extended in 2023
<br />
<br />There is no need to submit special documents for the extension of payments. The decision was made during the discussions between the representative of the Commissioner for the rights of citizens affected by the armed aggression against Ukraine, Olga Altunina, representatives of the Ministry of Social Policy, the Ministry of Reintegration, the Pension Fund of Ukraine, as well as specialized NGOs, said Dmytro Lubinets, the Verkhovna Rada Commissioner for Human Rights.
<br />
<br />Thus, in order to receive housing allowance, internally displaced persons will not need to provide supporting documents on their financial situation, since the receipt of this assistance does not depend on the income received and is unlimited, he adds.
